SIMPLE: flatness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flatness
<hw>flat"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being flat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Evenness of surface; want of relief or prominence;
the state of being plane or level.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Want of vivacity or spirit; prostration; dejection;
depression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Want of variety or flavor; dullness;
insipidity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Depression of tone; the state of being below the
true pitch; -- opposed to <contr>sharpness</contr> or
<contr>acuteness</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flatour</ent>⟦br⟧
